padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">730</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":730,\"repo\":\"RigsOfRods/rigs-of-rods\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Soft-Body physics simulator for vehicles and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T10:12:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Standalone Code Points</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p>The code points of the Unicode blocks <a href=\"https://codepoints.net/box_drawing\">Box\nDrawing</a> (U+2500 to U+257F) and <a href=\"https://codepoints.net/block_elements\">Block\nElements</a> (U+2580 to U+259F) cover\nmost of your monospace command-line visualization needs.</p>\n<pre><code>  ╭───────╮\n  │Unicode│\n  │rules! │\n  ╰┬─────┬╯\n</code></pre>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T07:15:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Record Holders and Extremes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+0000\">U+0000</a> &#x3C;control> - first code point.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T07:15:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Record Holders and Extremes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+0F33\">U+0F33</a> TIBETAN DIGIT HALF ZERO - code point that\nrepresents the <em>lowest</em> “single-digit” number and at the same time the\nonly negative one, -½.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T07:15:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Codepoints/awesome-codepoints","categoryHTML":"<h2>Record Holders and Extremes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>The trophy for most useless code points goes to\n<a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+0080\">U+0080</a>,\n<a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+0081\">U+0081</a> and\n<a href=\"https://codepoints.net/U+0099\">U+0099</a>. These so-called C1 control\ncharacters are more or less unspecified. They got into Unicode, because\nthey were present in the very first version of what should later become ISO\n10646, the ISO-standardized version of Unicode. They <a href=\"http://unicode.org/mail-arch/unicode-ml/y2015-m10/0050.html\">were meant to be part\nof an upgrade to ISO\n2022</a>, that\nnever came to be.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T07:15:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"yenchenlin/awesome-watchos","categoryHTML":"<h1>Books</h1>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.raywenderlich.com/store/watchos-2-by-tutorials\">watchOS 2 by Tutorials</a></p>\n<p><space><space>&#x3C;img src=\"<a href=\"http://cdn5.raywenderlich.com/wp-content/themes/raywenderlich/images/store-2015/w2t_PDF_640.png\">http://cdn5.raywenderlich.com/wp-content/themes/raywenderlich/images/store-2015/w2t_PDF_640.png</a>\") alt=\"Example App\" width=\"320\"/></space></space></p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T06:08:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"RomanTsegelskyi/rbooks","categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science</h2>","itemHTML":"<h4>Mastering Data Science with R <a href=\"https://www.packtpub.com/big-data-and-business-intelligence/mastering-data-analysis-r\">[Packt]</a></h4>\n<img src=\"https://www.packtpub.com/sites/default/files/2028OS_1981_Mastering%20Data%20Analysis%20with%20R.jpg\" width=\"200px\">\n<p>This book will give you the guidance you need to build and develop your knowledge and expertise. Bridging the gap between theory and practice, this book will help you to understand and use data for a competitive advantage.</p>\n<p>Beginning with taking you through essential data mining and management tasks such as munging, fetching, cleaning, and restructuring, the book then explores different model designs and the core components of effective analysis. You will then discover how to optimize your use of machine learning algorithms for classification and recommendation systems beside the traditional and more recent statistical methods.</p>","updatedAt":"2015-10-21T05:13:15.000Z"}]}},"pageContext":{"type":"day","from":1445385600000,"to":1445471999999,"previousId":"2015-10-22","nextId":"2015-10-20","nextName":"Oct 20th, 2015","previousName":"Oct 22nd, 2015"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}